The paper presents a navigation system for robots that combines hierarchical planning and machine learning. The system uses deep local trajectory planning and velocity control to compute motion commands, which suggests that it falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of attention mechanisms in the system's execution makes it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions simulation experiments, which suggests that it may fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY).
